# When present, EAS Build uses this INSTEAD of .gitignore to decide what to
# upload. It exists for exactly one reason: `webroot/` is gitignored (it is a
# build artifact) but must reach the build, because `expo prebuild` runs on
# the EAS worker and the `withWebroot` plugin copies the tree into the native
# projects there.
#
# Without this file the upload would honour .gitignore, drop `webroot/`, and
# the plugin would fail the build — or, if the guard in withWebroot.js were
# ever relaxed, ship an app whose WebView loads a 404. Keep `webroot/`
# absent from this list.

node_modules/
.expo/
dist/
ios/
android/
*.log
